Just recently, Ozonna Soludo, a fast rising singer and entrepreneur, widely recognized as the first son of Anambra State Governor, Professor Charles Chukwuma Soludo, won the hearts of many with new photos of himself, which he released on social media to celebrate Nigeria’s Democracy Day. The new photos were released on his official Instagram account, where he is known for constantly sharing photos and videos of himself to keep his fans entertained and glued to his page. In the new photos, the first son of the sitting governor was seen at his father’s office wearing a lovely matching outfit while he complemented the outfit with a red cap and black shoes.

While releasing the photos, he added a caption that reads;
“Happy Democracy Day to Nigeria. Though we have some ways to go to be in alignment with our coat of arms there is still so much to love & celebrate! Mad love to Naija. #June12th.”
Check Out The Screenshot Of His Caption Below
As expected, immediately after the post surfaced online, his fans and social media followers, quickly rushed down to the comment box section to express their reactions from different perspectives.
